rwood Stewart]] || 1\u20136, 7\u20135, 6\u20133\n|- style=\"background:#ccf;\"\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss || 1979 || US Open || {{flagicon|USA}} Bob Lutz || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Peter Fleming (tennis)|Peter Fleming]]<br />{{flagicon|USA}} [[John McEnroe]] || 2\u20136, 4\u20136\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss || 1980 || Wimbledon || {{flagicon|USA}} Bob Lutz || {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Peter McNamara]]<br />{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Paul McNamee]] || 6\u20137, 3\u20136, 7\u20136, 4\u20136\n|- style=\"background:#ccf;\"\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Win || 1980 || US Open || {{flagicon|USA}} Bob Lutz || {{flagicon|USA}} Peter Fleming<br />{{flagicon|USA}} John McEnroe || 7\u20136, 3\u20136, 6\u20131, 3\u20136, 6\u20133\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss || 1981 || Wimbledon || {{flagicon|USA}} Bob Lutz || {{flagicon|USA}} Peter Fleming<br />{{flagicon|USA}} John McEnroe || 4\u20136, 4\u20136, 4\u20136\n|}\n\n==Career finals==\n<small>Note: Smith won 10 titles before the Open Era</small>\n\n===Singles: 95 (65 titles, 30 runner-ups)===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n! style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n! W\u2013L\n! style=\"width:40px\"|Year\n! style=\"width:300px\"|Tournament\n! Surface\n! style=\"width:180px\"|Opponent\n! style=\"width:180px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98FB98\" | Win\n| <small>1\u20130</small>\n| 1964\n| Pasadena Metropolitan, Pasadena\n| ?\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Robert Potthast\n| 6\u20131, 3\u20136, 6\u20133\n|-\n| style=\"background:#FFA07A\" | Loss\n| <small>1\u20131</small>\n| 1965\n| Ojai Championships, Ojai\n| ?\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Charlie Pasarell]]\n| 3\u20136, 1\u20136\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98FB98\" | Win\n| <small>2\u20131</small>\n| 1965\n| Tucson Invitation, Tucson\n| ?\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Allen Fox]]\n| 6\u20131, 4\u20136, 8\u20136\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98FB98\" | Win\n| <small>3\u20131</small>\n| 1966\n| Western Indoor Championship,